@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Copyright"
@prev "Main"

Basically, this programs places an AppIcon on the workbench, to act as a
Trashcan. There are quite a few variants on this same theme, but this
program works in a similar way to that of the Apple Mac's trashcan.

Icons dropped on the AppIcon will me moved to a directory called
'Trashcan', in the root directory of the same volume.

To empty all the trashcans in all available volumes, a menu item in the
Workbench Tools menu is added, 'Empty Trash'. Selecting this will delete
all files in all available trashcans.

NB: This program is Shareware, see @{ "Copyright" link Copyright }.

The new cli commands, EmptyTrash and Trash, with this version are exact
equivalents to the Tools Menu and AppIcon methods of trashing.

The features include: (+) new in this version.

      o Trashcan AppIcon.
      o 'Empty Trash' tools menu item.
      o Customisable AppIcon icon.
      o Customisable AppIcon name.
      o Customisable position on the Workbench.
      o Customisable tools menu item name.
      o EmptyTrash cli command. (+)
      o Trash cli command. (+)
      o Optional ability to only to not operate on specified volumes. (+)

Requirements:

      o Kickstart v37+

To Do:

      o Localisation.

@endnode

